olive oil
2 potato
1 stalk celery
½ apple
1 packet beef mince
1 fine breadcrumbs
1 eggs
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 tsp honey
20 g butter
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Italian Truffle Mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks, then place on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 18-20 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery. Thinly slice apple (see ingredients) into sticks.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, fine breadcrumbs, the egg, Aussie spice blend and a pinch of salt.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of beef mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.

Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the ingredients and shaping the mixture into meatballs!

• When the potatoes have 5 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey and turn meatballs to coat.

• In a small heatproof bowl, melt the butter in the microwave.
• Remove tray from the oven, then crush potatoes until 1cm-thick. Drizzle over melted butter and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
• Roast until golden, a further 8-10 minutes.

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling the cheese on top.

• Meanwhile, combine celery, apple, shredded cabbage mix and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.

• Divide beef meatballs, cheesy roast potatoes and apple slaw between plates.
• Serve with Italian truffle mayonnaise. Enjoy!